localString.value: Sick to death of hearing about the prowess of mages like Elminster, Blackstaff, and the Red Wizards of Thay; Klaphen Fortier, a powerful, but relatively unknown wizard, created these robes to bolster young spellcasters across the realms. His hope was that youthful and unscrupulous mages might be encouraged to challenge more powerful wizards in hopes of making a name for themselves. Rumor has it that Klaphen died in an accident of spectacular proportions, when 56 lightning bolts and numerous large meteors struck his tower.
Designed by the wizard Malket, these robes provide comfort and utility...the caster's movements are uninhindered and pouches ensure strategic placement of material components.

This Tome allows you to chose the creature you want to summon. Simply use the Special Power, then chose the Spell Level and the creature you want to summon with your next spell of that level. This creature will be summoned every time you chose to cast a spell from that level.

The grease covered contraption before you contains the necessary tools, clamps, cutter, vials and other assorted bits needed to use the tinkering skill. A tinkerer tool is needed to activate and use parts of the set.
